website_summaries.verdict: For $100, the comfortable Jabra Wireless headphone pair delivers solid Bluetooth audio that will appeal to bass lovers.
pros: Powerful audio performance with deep bass response and clear, bright highs
cons: Not for purists seeking flat response

customer_reviews.title: Be wary that the purchase matches the picture in the supplier,s advert.
customer_reviews.text: Genuine EU Jabra headphones come with printed info on the cups, two tone colour on headband and the vol/ multi function buttons should be as in the official manual. Amazon supplied headphones which were like 'fake'.....really pissed off with Chinese products in general.
customer_reviews.author: Alan Purvis

customer_reviews.title: No surprises... good, workmanlike headphones
customer_reviews.text: Bought the black pair for around £50 after having read positive reviews in a number of publications including techradar and Whathifi. Overall quite pleased with them, fit is comfortable, headphones are lightweight. The sound is reasonable well balanced, bass is present but not over emphasised. Wireless connection seems solid and I've had no problems. Only had them a few days so can't speak for longevity of the product. Overall seem very good value for money for £50. Also, comfortable to wear with glasses which is always a big plus!
customer_reviews.author: Sean Rees

customer_reviews.title: I also like the fact they are only £52 compared to the ...
customer_reviews.text: After looking a lots of wireless headphones, & comparing on different sites, I found these on tech radar site &I they came in 2nd place out of ten. I also like the fact they are only £52 compared to the ones selling for £200 / £300 They are easy to set up &a of good quality. The only thing I think could of been a bit better is the size of the on /off switch, but overall a great wireless headphone set for TV or Running etc.
customer_reviews.author: Sibbo19

customer_reviews.title: Excellent Headphones
customer_reviews.text: Bought these headphones over a year ago and have used them quite a lot. They really are brilliant for the money. Size is good and sound quality is close to the top end brands I’ve used. They feel solid and fit nice and comfortably on me. I’ve used them a lot for the gym and when running and again can’t fault them, never fallen off once. They connect mostly without issue, although for me sometimes connecting and iOS devices has been a bit hit and miss. They aren’t great for calls but I’m not gonna mark that down cause they are so good for the money! All in all, excellent.
customer_reviews.author: Marc

customer_reviews.title: I could not recommend these headphones enough.
customer_reviews.text: Absolutely brilliant headphones. They really are incredible for the price. Sound quality is very good and build quality is pretty decent. I'd be surprised to find a better pair of headphones for the same price. The only complaint I do have is with these being On-Ear Headphones they can get a bit uncomfortable if you're wearing them for a few hours, like I do at work. They are however very comfortable for short amounts of time i.e commuting, walking etc.
customer_reviews.author: Connorlee123

customer_reviews.title: Great for the Gym!
customer_reviews.text: Got these on a Black Friday Deal. The Mrs uses them at the gym and unlike her previous wireless headphones they don't move or slip when she is running or going full beast mode. Keep an eye out for any upcoming deals to get it at a great price but the product itself is pretty damn good!
customer_reviews.author: Matt

customer_reviews.title: Nice! (& how to turn off audio hints)
customer_reviews.text: They look premium, lightweight and with good sound quality, both in bluetooth mode or with the audio cable (included). To turn off the audio guidance, low battery, etc, just follow the steps: - turn off the headphones (switch button to battery position) and wait 30sec - press and hold 'volume down' button - while holding the volume down button, turn the headphones on (switch button to bluetooth position) All in all, very good headphones. A small remark, no carry case included, which is a shame.
customer_reviews.author: Solaris

customer_reviews.title: Poor quality
customer_reviews.text: Stopped working properly after 3 months - keeps losing the sound. No ability to contact seller, so sadly cannot send it back for a repair.
customer_reviews.author: S Tan

customer_reviews.title: Happy as larry
customer_reviews.text: No problems connecting to my android phone or computer. Sounds great but I'm no audio expert. I do have a pair of Sennheiser Mx 400 and these are not too far off and these are much better than Jam Fusions I also own. Comfort is good so I can wear for hours Update : I've owned these for a year and still working really well. Battery life seems to go on for ages and sounds quality decent. I'd point out they can leak sound so don't turn them too loud
customer_reviews.author: Mr L

customer_reviews.title: Does what it says on the tin
customer_reviews.text: I bought these for gym use, and after daily use for a few months I can say they stand up. The sound quality is superior but it does enough to hear it clearly and over the background of a busy gym. They are fairly comfortable and sit on top of the ears (the max I will wear these is about 2 hours), battery life is good, I charge them about once a week. Durable, haven't had them break or crack and I'm fairly rough with them. Got them in a prime sale for £35 and I'd recommend.
customer_reviews.author: RB

customer_reviews.title: I am torn on these
customer_reviews.text: They are light, easy to connect but... when im on a call with someone everything echoes outside. I can hear a pin drop in the street ... at the same time the person im talking to says i sound like i’m in a tin can.. Further to that today i connected and only the right side works & i’m not a heavy user at all. Pity my return window closed end of Jan.. how do i send these back to be fixed !!!!!
customer_reviews.author: Adlu swan

customer_reviews.title: Excellent Value
customer_reviews.text: Bought these for the gym as in ear ones kept falling out. They look great ( not to bulky) and stay in place through all workouts. The sound quality is very good and connects instantly every time. I can leave my phone in the locker and have never had any drop out. Overall very happy with these and when you look at the price of some brands I think that these are great value - love them!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Excellent for the price
customer_reviews.text: I saw these highly reviewed in a tech publication and decided to give them a go. For 40 quid they are excellent. They are comfortable, easy to use, the sound quality is good and they look stylish. As they are on-ear the sound cancellation is not great but otherwise they are great all round. I particularly like the on/off/pairing switch which is a big improvement over previous bluetooth devices I have tried which require complicated series of button presses to pair with your phone. Definite recommendation.
customer_reviews.author: Gary

customer_reviews.title: Great sound quality
customer_reviews.text: These headphones are superb. Great sound quality, well built and nicely designed. They're sometimes a bit fiddly to pair and automatically connect to my laptop over-riding my mobile if both items are in the same room. Other than that, absolutely no issues. Would definitely recommend.
customer_reviews.author: McComa

customer_reviews.title: Too small
customer_reviews.text: I'm lucky enough to have a set of Jabra Evolve 65 Bluetooth headphones so wanted to buy another, but cheaper, set of Jabra 'phones. I opted for this model. Sadly they're not nearly as good. The sound is great – no problems there, but what I don't like is the fit. I found the headband too tight even with the full adjustment, and the ear cups too small, and my head is slightly smaller than average for an adult. Perhaps they're designed for children? The controls for volume are also small and difficult to find. I sent them back for a refund feeling disappointed as, based on my experience with the Evolve 'phones, I thought these would be great.
customer_reviews.author: frog

customer_reviews.title: mediocre
customer_reviews.text: Pro's: Nice looking, pairs quickly & easily, comfortable Cons: poor bass & treble, bt range not great, poor fit & headband creaks Music was lacking some bass and treble detail. Bluetooth signal started to break-up around 7/8 metres (from upstairs to downstairs through stud walls and floorboards only, from my office to my kitchen). These slide off my head when I look down (150mm ear to ear) and the headband creaks when moved. Also, the sliding sides are far too loose.
customer_reviews.author: Stuart

customer_reviews.title: If you're hesitating, don't. You won't find better on ear bluetooth headphones than these beauties.
customer_reviews.text: Absolutely perfect. I wear them walking, I wear them in the gym, and I wear them on public transport. I've had them for less than a week and I can't imagine how I managed without them. They sit comfortably on my ears, firm enough a fit so that they don't slip, but no so firm that they're uncomfortable. I just wore them for 90 mins in the gym and I could have worn them for 90 more mins they're so comfy. The bass is great, not boosted, just natural and rich. Really good looking, attracting loads of compliments, with a great sound and instant bluetooth connection.
customer_reviews.author: Angela

customer_reviews.title: Great product
customer_reviews.text: Really very happy with my headphones. Only one little thing. When I watch tv on my phone they do hold up programs (i.e. Busy/loading circle appears). It's happens at least once a programme. Not sure why. Doesn't happen with plug in headphones. Guess it's because they are Bluetooth. However, I was warned that when using wireless headphones to watch tv, the sound might not be synched up with picture. This has not been a problem with these headphones. Worth the money.
customer_reviews.author: McStan

customer_reviews.title: Good Sound Quality but Uncomfortable to Wear
customer_reviews.text: These headphones have a good sound quality, however, they are uncomfortable to wear for extended periods - especially if you wear spectacles. The earpieces are a little on the small side and there is a lot of pressure on the ear which push the top of the ear against the spectacles arm - it really is very uncomfortable. Also on the down side is that there is no stowage case with this item,
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Quickly Faulty and No Response from Seller
customer_reviews.text: Within two months these headphones have stopped working properly and the seller has ignored my request for a refund. Sound through them constantly stutters and sometimes using the play button on the headphones causes music to come out of the phone.
customer_reviews.author: Yussef

customer_reviews.title: Rich sound and comfortable
customer_reviews.text: I'm really surprised by these headphones given the price. They are really nice design, sturdy and look great. Advantages: Bluetooth/wireless Cable included for connecting to devices Charging cable included Battery life of about 8hrs Great sound Sturdy design Comfortable and lightweight Disadvantages: Sound leakage No noise isolation My last headphones were big and bulky. These are smart, slimline, comfortable to wear and offer great sound. Real bargin for your money.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Be careful of MUTE not working...
customer_reviews.text: I bought these headphones for running and the gym and they work very well and are super comfortable. The sound quality is great and they are pretty durable. I do a lot of conference calls for work, so will sometimes use these during calls. However, I recently discovered that when you MUTE your phone, the headset microphone is not muted. A massive design flaw from Jabra, but a word of warning to all of you out there who use the MUTE function. I would have given these 5 stars if it weren't for this.
customer_reviews.author: April Lachlan

customer_reviews.title: Poor quality
customer_reviews.text: They are very comfortable and light, and they connect easy enough. Just in time for the return window to close they started breaking up in the seam however, so very soon they will be un-wearable. Not too happy about this! Wouldn't recommend buying.
customer_reviews.author: Joakim Tönnberg

customer_reviews.title: Great except the sound
customer_reviews.text: These are well made, comfortable headphones. They are stable on the head. Pairing is simple and reliable, the bluetooth range is excellent and the controls are all convenient. However, the sound is poor. The sound stage is narrow and closed, the mid-range is sacrificed to bass and treble making voices muddled and frequently they sound harsh. There are better choices in the price range.
customer_reviews.author: Mr. PT Farrell

customer_reviews.title: Ok budget Bluetooth headphones
customer_reviews.text: They worked in the most part. Sometimes have connection issues and skipping when first connected. When connected sound good. Battery is pretty good too. I wear glasses so some times have to remove as my ears start to ache. Comfort was the main reason I stopped wearing these. So
customer_reviews.author: Trevor

customer_reviews.title: They are good quality with great sound and fit perfectly
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these headphones for my husband who is a postman. He uses the everyday while out working and wouldn't be without them. They are good quality with great sound and fit perfectly. They are good value for the money and would both recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Run_in_Heels1

customer_reviews.title: but very good. Bluetooth connection working well
customer_reviews.text: My first pair of bluetooth cans.. Lightweight and quite comfy to wear. Sound quality .. perhaps not top grade HI-FI, but very good. Bluetooth connection working well.
customer_reviews.author: Gerry935

customer_reviews.title: Fantastic value for the price
customer_reviews.text: For the price these cost, they're fantastic. I was planning on buying a much more expensive pair when someone pointed these out. Sound is excellent and they're very comfortable. My only small issues is that on VERY rare occasions, the Bluetooth connection can get a bit dodgy but that requires a quick restart. Another small gripe is that after long periods of wearing these on your ears, your ears tend to get hot.
customer_reviews.author: TSJ

customer_reviews.title: Best non-premium I’ve heard and amazing price.
customer_reviews.text: Really good quality and great sound, no issues with battery life. The only reason I’m not giving 5 star is that portable sound can be better but it’ll cost you 100s - for the reason that 5/5 is perfection, in my mind, can’t mislead you all and say that. These are definitely the best I’ve heard that cost less then £300 and that is a huge compliment. Surround sound on a movie is first class.
customer_reviews.author: Mike Archer

customer_reviews.title: I bought these after having been disappointed by some good looking but cheap bluetooth headphones in ...
customer_reviews.text: There's always a play-off between price and quality. I bought these after having been disappointed by some good looking but cheap bluetooth headphones in a discount shop. I can't say I've widely tested bluetooth headphones, at least not beyond these and the cheap ones! But they connect easily, charge quickly, they feel robust, look cool and sound pretty good to me and regularly came up best in reviews I'd seen of headphones in this price range. I'm very happy with them. Definitely worth making the leap to bluetooth - when you're wire-free you realise what a pain it was to be catching your headphone cable all the time!
customer_reviews.author: Farlsborough

customer_reviews.title: Excellent product for the money.
customer_reviews.text: This was a gift for my partner, he had been wanting wireless headphones for the gym but didn't want to pay the crazy price for the big brand items. After lots of searching and reading reviews, we decided to give these a go. Safe to say we went disappointed. They look great and the sound is fantastic. I don't like big headphones but have found myself borrowing these at every opportunity. They do take a little while to fully charge, but charge lasts a good week of gym sessions. Only issue we have found is this model isn't compatible with the app.
customer_reviews.author: Lj0ns3y

customer_reviews.title: Expertly Made Wireless Headphones
customer_reviews.text: Bought as a gift for someone else, but checked them out beforehand. Can confirm that these headphones are great. Well made, sturdy and decent audio quality. Bass is beefy enough and there's no lack of definition in the high end. Easy to start using and pair with any device, and the earpieces are nice and comfortable. When my wired headphones inevitably break, I'll probably be buying a pair of these for myself
customer_reviews.author: Paul Beal

customer_reviews.title: The old Jabra Move was better.
customer_reviews.text: Sorry guys, I like the product, somehow, however the product got worse comparing with the previous model: 1) You have now an annoying, loud and repetitive message of device not connected everytime you are connecting to bluetooth (old version was a simple beep when connected) 2) It is not always connecting to iPhone 7 even after saying 'connected', so you end up going to bluetooth settings to add the device manually or to at least confirm it's connected 3) the previous model was more comfortable to the ears Almost like I want to guess that you (unfortunately) changed your chief designer to build the new model.
customer_reviews.author: Ramiro Castro

customer_reviews.title: Excellent versatile headphones
customer_reviews.text: Bought for my 12 year old daughter who is an avid gamer. She has them synced with every device she has and also uses them to chat with her friends while gaming online. They have a great sound and also can be used with a cable aswell which is good when they run out of charge. The headphones are well made and sturdy.
customer_reviews.author: Elaine Coller

customer_reviews.title: OMG I'm Love!
customer_reviews.text: Best bluetooth headphones I've purchased, sound, comfort and style is A+. I bought and returned a Sony WC-CH700N because it was big and sounded horrible I then gave my son my replacement Sony MDRXB650BTB.CE7 which was better in sound quality but still not what I expected This Jabra Move is perfect and at the reduced price of £39.99 is one I would certainly recommend
customer_reviews.author: Gary "Ricksy"

customer_reviews.title: Can’t go wrong
customer_reviews.text: The sound is brilliant the volume level is higher than needed, the connectivity to phone in pocket and all soundbars I’ve tried is excellant the battery life after charge is high I haven’t had it run out on me unexpectedly yet. Minor gripe a bit rigid on the head but easily livable and they don’t look as good as they sound, impressed and well worth the money
customer_reviews.author: Rogeroo33

customer_reviews.title: Great sound but broke in no time at all
customer_reviews.text: I bought 2 pairs of these Jabra wireless headsets as Christmas presents and both have now broken as the weld has failed in the same place on both of them. It is where the ear piece is attached to the headband. It, therefore, seems to be a general product issue rather than a one off. The sound still comes out but they are now not usable. I'm really disappointed as I bought Jabra on the back of using Jabra products at work and I was impressed with those ones.
customer_reviews.author: Mrs H J Williams

customer_reviews.title: Poor quality - zero customer service
customer_reviews.text: These headphones have split at the seams, they crackle and have a bad connection. I wish to return them, but I am being 'blocked' from doing so!
customer_reviews.author: CJ

customer_reviews.title: Descent Headphones for the price
customer_reviews.text: These headphones are quality for the price paid. Sound quality is good. Too bad it has no noise cancellation. I used them for some time but finally admitted I needed to get noise cancellation headphones. Not the best if you commute to work in underground or other noisy environments.
customer_reviews.author: Ant123

customer_reviews.title: Pretty good overall
customer_reviews.text: The sound quality is perfect and the build is pretty good. The cups seem a little smaller than I'd of hoped for and don't remain in place all that well if doing something physical. The battery lasts a reasonable amount of time and is quick to charge. It connects easily to my android phone and MacBook. The wireless range is good.
customer_reviews.author: Jonah73

customer_reviews.title: Excellent sound quality with loud deep bass!
customer_reviews.text: If you've been using the same boring cheap headset and decided to upgrade, look no further! The clarity and sound quality of this thing produces is simply amazing. Some song with full volume will vibrate your ears with its loud bass!! Go to Utube and search for bass boosted song. You will understand what i mean.
customer_reviews.author: Faizal N.

customer_reviews.title: Never heard of these but they were branded the best on tech radar
customer_reviews.text: Never heard of these but they were branded the best on tech radar. Been really good quality sound and build wise. 100% value for money
customer_reviews.author: L J Livesey

customer_reviews.title: Some Niggles
customer_reviews.text: Double-duty controls are annoying, slips off my head a lot, and microphonics can be poor depending on the placement over the ear–however I tend to notice this more than most people. 'Low battery' warning at 40/50% is just plain stupid and annoying. But. Sound quality is good, they're well made, the connection is rock solid, standard charging lead, they can work wired and they don't look ridiculous. Pros greatly outweigh cons.
customer_reviews.author: Mr. A. F. Smith

customer_reviews.title: Best Bluetooth headphones
customer_reviews.text: I had loads of pairs of Bluetooth. These are the best. Because they are made of metal they don’t break. I go to bed with them on every night, I wake up and I’ve thrown them somewhere during the night and they aren’t broken and they are still charged.
customer_reviews.author: SHUTTERS

customer_reviews.title: Too Fragile
customer_reviews.text: Nice design but very poorly made. I bought these for my son, who liked them, but they dropped from his head once and broke when they hit the ground. One earpiece broke from the blue plastic rear cup, and one of the two fine audio cables inside also broke from where it was soldered to the main circuit board. I could see that one of three very flimsy plastic grooves holding the earpiece in had broken, and was too small to repair. Very disappointed these headphones broke so easily and so soon after buying them (4 weeks).
customer_reviews.author: Pakhead

customer_reviews.title: Solid Headphones
customer_reviews.text: Sound quality wise it's not as great as I hoped especially in comparison to my Sony MDR1a from 4 years ago and, especially after reading the review on TechRadar. But the Move is solid, good sound quality, and extremely comfy and holds on snug and firmly. You'd have to move around wildly to get it to come off. It blocks out sound very well but too loud and it will leak sound without even being on max volume. Overall I'm very happy with my purchase
customer_reviews.author: Lionel Sheriff

customer_reviews.title: bought these 3 months ago and they worked perfect, however
customer_reviews.text: bought these 3 months ago and they worked perfect, however, recently they developed an incredibly annoying habit of breaking the connection, especially when i'm in the gym (this never happened when i first started using them). imagine how frustrating it is to have your workout soundtrack cut every 2 seconds when you're trying to lift. seems like whenever i would cover the right earphone with my hand, it would cut off the signal altogether. sometimes signal breaks when i'm just walking down the street with the ipod either in my bag or in my pocket. tl;dr everything was peachy creamy until after 3 months of use.
customer_reviews.author: Miss N Bolgarova

customer_reviews.title: Great sound for the money, very comfortable.
customer_reviews.text: Amazing headphones for the money. After 18 months they still hold up very well although the leather ear cups have become a bit rough and flaked a bit but that’s due to the stubble on my face. Only issues are it sometimes drops the connection and needs to be re-paired when turning on in high traffic environments. Battery is ok. Very lightweight.
customer_reviews.author: Michael Rhys Morgan

customer_reviews.title: Good Buy
customer_reviews.text: First impressions are excellent. Had them a couple of days, easy to connect, sound quality is good enough and ease of use superb. Bought them after reading a very favourable review. What I was looking for was an inexpensive headphone that could be used at work, travelling etc that were inexpensive. So far they have ticked all those boxes.
customer_reviews.author: D J Lee

customer_reviews.title: I am glad I got them.
customer_reviews.text: These have lasted a couple of years and are still in use. The fabric on the ear pieces is very thin and has worn away but they still work well. Just the odd blip of confused connection and when I turn my head to the right, sound cuts out but in one way- that’s quite good if you’re crossing a road and you’re looking left and right! I think I would buy these again. When I am listening with them, I can’t hear anything else around me. I have to lip-read.
customer_reviews.author: Another customer

customer_reviews.title: call quality is not very good. not worth buying
customer_reviews.text: Worked well initially. left ear piece has stopped working. call quality is not very good. not worth buying.
customer_reviews.author: AA

customer_reviews.title: Jabra Move - Great headphones for music and phone calls.
customer_reviews.text: Really like these Jabra headphones, work great with my iPhone 7 for listening to music and making calls. Can use them easily all week for travelling to and from work without the need for charging. Sound quality is good for music and they are very comfortable to wear for extended periods. Only dropped a star because being a premium product I would have expected a carry case or bag to be supplied, luckily I had a spare one laying around.
customer_reviews.author: Adrenachrome

customer_reviews.title: Loose fit, bad bluetooth connection
customer_reviews.text: These aren't high end headphones. I switched to them after I lost my Marshall monitors, and they're definitely not as good. However, that being said, they're very comfortable, light and well designed. The sound quality is good for the price bracket. They seem pretty durable, too. Update: These headphones tend to become very loose and fall off your head after some use. This has also happened with my friend's headphones. Another thing is the bluetooth connection is very poor and lags.
customer_reviews.author: Peter Roberts

customer_reviews.title: Very good heaphones. Im happy!
customer_reviews.text: Excellent sound quality. Comfortable fit. Stylish design. Faultless Bluetooth connectivity (so far). Pricey but well worth it, in my opinion. (The blue ones seem to be more expensive than the red or black ones, for some strange reason.
customer_reviews.author: Zob

customer_reviews.title: Great sound, poor build quality.
customer_reviews.text: Had these for 1 year. They sound good & are nice & comfortable but they're starting to come apart inside the ear cups. Bluetooth connectivity is reliable with everything except my two Samsung Android phones which often fail to connect for media use.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Poor battery life
customer_reviews.text: The battery life is really bad on my pair - I use them for about 3 hours a day, they were fully charged on Sunday evening and were out of battery by 8am on Tuesday. Whats more frustrating is that my pair don't give any warning, apart from beeping 3 times every 20 seconds 20 minutes before the battery goes, when it's both a useless and extremely irritating warning. Such a shame because I like the sound quality and they work well otherwise but I can't be bothered having to charge them every single day.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great headphones supported by excellent customer service.
customer_reviews.text: Purchased these bluetooth headphones for my son Christmas 2018, he uses them everyday paired to his phone to listen to music and video and they have been brilliant. After 18 months constant use the headphones just stopped charging (no problems experienced leading up to this fault). Reported to Jabra customer service, who were very responsive and replaced the headphone with the latest model very promptly. Excellent customer service, highly recommend Jabra, based on this purchase and post sales customer experience.
customer_reviews.author: Mr Lee J Fawcett

customer_reviews.title: To loose on head.
customer_reviews.text: Cons Fit - Not very tight on head, so sound quality and volume suffer, also feel quite loose and could fall off. The ear cup is very small Pro's Design is nice and simple Value for money, they are not great but at this price they are fine Light weight Somewhat comfortable
customer_reviews.author: Aaron

customer_reviews.title: Great Headphones. Amazing value for money.
customer_reviews.text: Great headphones. Amazing value for money. Super easy to pair. Really great for when active/moving as they stay really tight to the head while being comfy. Sound quality and volume is very pleasing plus the amount of background noise I experienced while using them was very low. The external controls on the headphones are pretty useful for audio as well as some other helpful functions. My partner bought the pair in red a day after mine arrived and now we both use them whenever we're exercising, commuting, studying etc. Also look really nice.
customer_reviews.author: Richard Anley

customer_reviews.title: The sound from these is good and they are comfortable to wear and its a ...
customer_reviews.text: The sound from these is good and they are comfortable to wear and its a doddle to set them up. They do have a regular attendance to drop connection with your device but this could be the headphone or the device. Biggest issue with these is whilst the head band is robust and good quality the padded ear pieces are not and after only a couple of months the stitching comes away from the shell and they disintegrate. But its only £50.
customer_reviews.author: I. lapsley

customer_reviews.title: Not worth it
customer_reviews.text: After about 6 months these headphones lose their connection frequently some times for hours on end. I wrote to their customer support there was no reply. The sound leakage is awful and they are not suitable for exercising (running just about but, nothing else).
customer_reviews.author: J

customer_reviews.title: Nice, reliable and comfortable
customer_reviews.text: I use these headphones for the gym and since theyre lying in my gym bag i dont charge them often and they last a long time with one charge. I dont charge them for weeks sometimes. theyre pretty comfortable on the ear and theres loads of room for adjustement. would definetely recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Siraj

customer_reviews.title: Overall good value for money(great sound)
customer_reviews.text: They are pretty good. Pretty comfortable but not as comfortable as my old plantronics just because they are a bit heavier. Easy to adjust, decent battery life if you’re a light user. Great sound. Overall pretty happy with the quality for the price.
customer_reviews.author: Virgil Tanase

customer_reviews.title: This product has a great build, feels sturdy and looks awesome
customer_reviews.text: This product has a great build, feels sturdy and looks awesome. But I had to return it due to the sound leakage being quite high.
customer_reviews.author: Raj

customer_reviews.title: Good value
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these on Amazon warehouse for £20. They are a good pair of headphones for general use. The sound for the price is reasonable - I enjoy listening to audio books and the tv. For those who are more serious about musical detail and wish to have a serious listening experience I would invest somewhere else.
customer_reviews.author: Matthew J. Hanson

customer_reviews.title: Excellent value for money.
customer_reviews.text: Very nicely built. Size is perfect to fit on even large size ears, cancelling outside noise. Battery lasts and lasts...very good battery times. Easily connects with both computers, Android devices and iPhones. Great sound quality and sturdy.
customer_reviews.author: RedBox

customer_reviews.title: Dont buy any others at this price range!
customer_reviews.text: Fantastic product, great value and prompt delivery! These are soe of the best sounding headphone I own and they produce a very accurate treble and bass. Connect to my iphone quickly and easily, never drop bluetooth signal, cannot recommend enough! Battery lasts for around 20+ hours - brilliant!
customer_reviews.author: Sean J.

customer_reviews.title: They easily compared in the sounds department with ample punchy base ...
customer_reviews.text: Had the revos and beats studios prior to these. They easily compared in the sounds department with ample punchy base and excellent nights. Packaging was first class as was the build quality. My only negative ( being follicily challenged) was that with any movement forward or backwards at the gym, they would simply slip off my averaged sized head
customer_reviews.author: Karl999

customer_reviews.title: How long will they last?
customer_reviews.text: Even a few years later, these are still going! Build quality is fantastic! There is some flaking of the earpads but that's to be expected. Battery isn't as good as it used to be but in its prime you would easily get 5 days before having to charge again (using for around 6-8hrs a day). For me the earpads were a little small for my ears but they performed very well. The fact they're still being used is immense!
customer_reviews.author: Nick W.

customer_reviews.title: Excellent
customer_reviews.text: Great earphones and v easy to use, connect....music fidelity is always contentious, I found them to be great though. Passive noise cancellation is spot on. If you have glasses the headphones squeeze on them in protracted use so factor that in.
customer_reviews.author: White Rhino

customer_reviews.title: No problems; not uncomfortable after hours of use; decent sound
customer_reviews.text: No problems; not uncomfortable after hours of use (like most "on-ear" pairs for me); decent sound; battery lasts a reasonable amount of time; great for the price. Doesn't block out all sound, but that's expected for an "on-ear" pair rather than in/over ear.
customer_reviews.author: David Sanderson

customer_reviews.title: Bass lacks punch
customer_reviews.text: Just received these, and honestly, I'm disappointed by the sound. For the kind of music Iisten to (hip-hop, r&b or house), there's not enough base for me. My Bluedio T2S, which cost a third of the price, have a way fuller sound, with puncher bass. On the plus side, these are light, comfy, and have a clever controls for sound level, switching tracks, picking a call... But on the whole, this doesn't sound good enough to make them my daily about town headphones.
customer_reviews.author: Olivier Weber

customer_reviews.title: I love these headphones.
customer_reviews.text: These headphones are ace. They are very comfortable and the sound is perfect. I wanted them for my new iPad Pro and all of the other ones I looked at were much more expensive. If you are thinking about buying them, go ahead because I don't think that you could get anything better (not without spending hundreds more)
customer_reviews.author: Mrs. J. Findlay

customer_reviews.title: Great Bluetooth 'phones
customer_reviews.text: Great headphones. Battery lasts ages, sound is surprisingly good, and they're comfortable for extended periods of use. Occasionally flaky Bluetooth connection when first connecting - but don't know whether that's the headphones, or the phone, so can't mark it down for that. Good sound isolation with very little noise leakage. All in all very happy with the purchase.
customer_reviews.author: D. White

customer_reviews.title: Best wireless headphones I've had
customer_reviews.text: Excellent sound quality, easy to set up and, most importantly, really good battery life. I use these to commute and for the gym on a daily basis and they can go days before needing a charge. I've had them well over a year now and the battery life hasn't degraded over time. Recommended.
customer_reviews.author: JB

customer_reviews.title: Quality Product
customer_reviews.text: Headset not so comfortable over a longer period. Disappointed with switch arrangement for bluetooth integration. This is too small. Otherwise quality of sound perfectly acceptable. Perect of music and listening to sport events.
customer_reviews.author: Sammy 612008

customer_reviews.title: Nice for the price.
customer_reviews.text: Good set of headphones, light and comfortable, good range on Bluetooth and easy to pair. Only dropped one star as they are not quite as loud as my old set and on a plane I could still hear the engine but for the price the clarity is great.
customer_reviews.author: David F.

customer_reviews.title: Love them!
customer_reviews.text: Fantastic headphones for a brilliant price. Been looking for a good pair at a reasonable price for a long time and thought I’d give these a go and I absolutely love them. Great sound, just enough noise cancellation for me, very light and fit my head and ears like a glove. Bluetooth distance is great.
customer_reviews.author: Lrh

customer_reviews.title: best budget wireless headphones
customer_reviews.text: these wireless headphones are so good, there are light weight and sound very good with a fantastic battery life, this is my third life buying and it never disappoints.
customer_reviews.author: saim

customer_reviews.title: Great sound
customer_reviews.text: Bought one at Christmas for my son & he loves it. No expert about headphones but this has a great sound quality. Recommended.
customer_reviews.author: Mark Campbell

customer_reviews.title: The base hiss kills the enjoyment
customer_reviews.text: If you intend to listen to music, hiss is a distraction. Unfortunately this headset has a strong bse hiss which is evident all the time in dynamic music having quiet passages. Not enjoyable.
customer_reviews.author: Jari Aalto

customer_reviews.title: Cheap solo 3
customer_reviews.text: Price to performance is up there in the chart. For the sound quality I could say there is lot of bass, on par with my beats solo 3 . And the cherry on top is you can connect many devices at the same time to it ...
customer_reviews.author: Sina

customer_reviews.title: Great sound, slightly too quiet
customer_reviews.text: Very good sound, easy pairing, comfortable, stable connection. My only criticism is I could do with them going a bit louder on my Pixel 2 . I think Pixel 2 has quite low audio output because many headphones suffer with low volume, and these are better than many, but not quite as loud as the best. No problem with iPad though.
customer_reviews.author: Holmsey from Yorkshire

customer_reviews.title: Unbeatable value for a great lightweight set of headphones
customer_reviews.text: Brilliant set of headphones very comfy sound quality is awesome Only complaint is that while listening to ebooks on the train I can still hear people chatting but I guess that's to be expected Music does shut your the masses though
customer_reviews.author: Jane

customer_reviews.title: Awesome headphones
customer_reviews.text: Amazing headphones. Excellent quality of sound and the battery life is unbelievable. Great feature: wireless connection, wires free. Yay!!!
customer_reviews.author: Alee

customer_reviews.title: Excellent fit and comfort level
customer_reviews.text: These have lasted me over a year with 0 problems. Excellent fit and comfort level, good quality sound, lightweight and easy to use. The only annoying thing is that EVERY time you use them you have to listen to a bit of dialogue instructing you to connect via bluetooth. If you could get rid of that it would be perfect.
customer_reviews.author: Patrick H Jones

customer_reviews.title: Good quality cheap price
customer_reviews.text: All round outstanding, not had any issues. Perfect expecially for the price. Quality is top notch, cancels out nearly all noise, my pair survived a whole 6 hour constant music and still had life, i use them delivering for dpd so always in use and had a thorough test. And deapite bangs knocks and rain no damage or issues. Distance from phone is good too. Ideal for what i need them for and would hapily buy them again
customer_reviews.author: mark haywood

customer_reviews.title: Poor durability, great sound and ergonomics
customer_reviews.text: The quality of sound and ergonomics for this product is great, very happy but it has not survived wear at all. Images attached show the fabric has worn terribly, you get pieces of black appearing around your ear after wearing them when they reach this stage. No easy way to replace the fabric either, shame.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Jabra move
customer_reviews.text: I wrote a review criticising the sound level, I sorted the problem. My fault . These are really good headphones for the money. I would not hesitate to buy them again
customer_reviews.author: wilfrid mcneill

customer_reviews.title: Good headphones for the money
customer_reviews.text: Bought these for my 12 year old daughter. Pretty impressed. Easy to use/connect, decent sound quality, relatively lightweight and not too bass heavy. Look relatively well built too. The only problem is I may not be able to justify the more expensive pair I had my eyes on now!
customer_reviews.author: Mr. P. Sleigh

customer_reviews.title: Great quality headphone
customer_reviews.text: I'm happy with the headphone so far. It's light and comfortable on the head, delivering great sound as stated in the reviews I read. I wanted something decent to use with my iPod and found this headphone to be quality and within budget also.
customer_reviews.author: Felix A

customer_reviews.title: Quality and value
customer_reviews.text: Comfortable, neat and they sound great. I've yet to run out of battery life, so can't actually say how long they last. Better than other more expensive wired headphones I own too.
customer_reviews.author: Pete

customer_reviews.title: Brilliant
customer_reviews.text: I am blown away by the quality of these - build and sound. Maybe I'm not as experiences as others, but I think they are great. Bought them for my son, but I'm keeping them! I'll buy him a different pair! Had a bargain on price. If they come down again, I'll get a second pair for sure.
customer_reviews.author: Mjbzoom

customer_reviews.title: These are nice and provide good sound
customer_reviews.text: These are nice and provide good sound.. Unfortunatly after about 6 months of use the glue becomes unstuck around the earpieces and the foam becomes exposed.. It's a shame really. One of my friends also purchased a pair and the same thing happened to his. :(
customer_reviews.author: Mr W.

customer_reviews.title: Not the range I expected
customer_reviews.text: Overall its good, expensive headphones in the category but range is not what I expected, moving from living room to kitchen wnd zi started loosing the sound.
customer_reviews.author: US

customer_reviews.title: Wow!!!
customer_reviews.text: Wow wow wow...I was first told about these before I bought my expensive Sony's last year....I didn't listen....my Sony's are now broken after 13 months and so I bought these at a 1/3 of the price and they are absolutely amazing. Better quality at a fraction of the price.
customer_reviews.author: Alan

customer_reviews.title: Why pay fortunes when you can get these?
customer_reviews.text: These are great little headphones. Sound as good as any I have used before, easy to connect and hold a charge. Oh, comfy too. Amazing for the price.
customer_reviews.author: Paul Mumford

customer_reviews.title: Nice feel and build but average sound when used with ...
customer_reviews.text: Nice feel and build but average sound when used with my laptop. I have never used the volume control because its to fiddly to adjust when the headphones so leave them set to maximum which is OK because the headphones aren't very loud on the whole. The Bluetooth switch works well and connects without any problem. I need to try them with another sound source before I can say whether these headphones are good value or not
customer_reviews.author: JonA

customer_reviews.title: Fantastic headphones
customer_reviews.text: For the cost these are great noise cancelling headphones with excellent sound quality. The battery life is excellent as well - they don't need charged regularly.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Best at price point
customer_reviews.text: Got for 30 pound on offer very good price and value ... there are very well fitting ... cut outs all outside noise at half volume ....fit well And Iv onlyused 4-5 tines for 10 hours in total but connects first time and Bluetooth is fine
customer_reviews.author: james evans

Get a perfect fit with the ultra-light and comfortable headband.
